column13: This invention relates to a hanger for a rail comprising a support portion and a rail engaging portion wherein the support portion and the rail engaging portion are made substantially from dissimilar first and second plastics materials, respectively. The second plastics material has a greater yield strength than the first plastics material, that is to say the force required to deform or snap the first material is less than the force required to deform or snap the second material. This provides the advantage that a plastics material with a high yield strength may be used to form the rail engaging portion and a different plastics material which has a glossy attractive appearance and/or allows logos or text to be printed on the surface may be used to form the support portion.

This invention relates to a hanger (10; 110) for a rail comprising a support portion (12; 112) and a rail engaging portion (14; 114) wherein the support portion (12; 112) and the rail engaging portion (14; 114) are made substantially from dissimilar first and second plastics materials, respectively. The second plastics material has a greater yield strength than the first plastics material, that is to say the force required to deform or snap the first material is less than the force required to deform or snap the second material. This provides the advantage that a plastics material with a high yield strength may be used to form the rail engaging portion (14; 114) and a different plastics material which has a glossy attractive appearance and/or allows logos or text to be printed on the surface may be used to form the support portion (12; 112).
